WEBVTT

00:01.000 --> 00:03.754
FRANK: Previously on Hardy Boys.. .
TRUDY: How do you know Abigail Owens?

00:03.754 --> 00:04.671
- Wait, do you know her?

00:04.671 --> 00:06.173
- She was Demon Queen back in the day.

00:06.173 --> 00:07.382
- Guys, I think I found her.

00:07.382 --> 00:08.592
♪

00:08.592 --> 00:09.927
FRANK:
I knew Tom was our guy.

00:09.927 --> 00:11.136
Black boots, blue car.

00:11.136 --> 00:12.763
If we get our hands on that tape,

00:12.763 --> 00:14.723
then we figure out exactly
what happened to Dennis.

00:14.723 --> 00:16.350
Dennis:
Every time I try to remember, it hurts!

00:16.350 --> 00:18.268
- Well, try harder!
- Back off, Joe!

00:18.268 --> 00:20.479
- Where exactly were you
when he "hit his head"?

00:20.479 --> 00:21.855
- Stop, stop, stop!

00:21.855 --> 00:23.482
- I'm here for the tape.
I know you have it.

00:23.482 --> 00:25.359
Elroy:
I don't know what good it's gonna do you.

00:25.359 --> 00:27.319
I couldn't get it to play.
It's pretty water-damaged.

00:27.319 --> 00:30.280
GLORIA:
I want to mend fences with Francis.

00:30.280 --> 00:31.657
You get him to visit me here,

00:31.657 --> 00:34.368
and I'll put you back on track
for the life you deserve.

00:34.368 --> 00:36.662
Does he know you're here?

00:36.662 --> 00:38.789
- Are you seriously gonna keep
pretending like you weren't there?

00:38.789 --> 00:40.040
- Guys!
- What?!

00:40.040 --> 00:41.875
- You guys hear that?
[heavy breathing]

00:41.875 --> 00:43.752
[video static]

00:43.752 --> 00:44.753
- Dennis!

00:44.753 --> 00:46.380
JOE:
Someone got to him again.

00:46.380 --> 00:48.757
FRANK: If we put the wrong pieces
together, draw the wrong conclusions,

00:48.757 --> 00:50.217
there's gonna be consequences.

00:50.217 --> 00:51.343
- Night, boys.

00:51.343 --> 00:52.553
FRANK [on headphones]:
Night, Dad.

00:52.553 --> 00:55.222
JOE [on headphones]:
Maybe we should tell him about The Eye.

00:57.933 --> 01:00.936
[rain falling]
[thunder rumbling]

01:00.936 --> 01:03.272
[insects chirping]

01:03.272 --> 01:06.275
♪

01:07.818 --> 01:10.237
[thunder rumbling]
- What are you waiting for?

01:10.237 --> 01:13.490
[banging on glass]
- There's something at the window.

01:17.452 --> 01:19.746
[banging continues]
It wants in.

01:20.622 --> 01:21.999
We need to let it in.

01:23.041 --> 01:24.668
FRANK:
No, no, no, Joe. Wait one second.

01:24.668 --> 01:25.752
[loud thunder]

01:25.752 --> 01:27.337
[gasps, sighs]

01:27.337 --> 01:30.340
[knocking on window]

01:36.930 --> 01:39.099
[insects chirping]
What are you doing here? Something wrong?

01:39.099 --> 01:40.392
- Sorry, I didn't mean to wake you up.

01:40.392 --> 01:42.603
I just want to talk about something.

01:42.603 --> 01:44.813
- Of course, anything. What is it?

01:45.689 --> 01:46.815
- Tell her about the tape.

01:47.524 --> 01:48.942
- Oh, you're here, too.

01:49.401 --> 01:51.987
- Don't sound so disappointed.
CALLIE: I was just, um,

01:51.987 --> 01:54.865
I came to catch up on the case.
What tape?

01:56.200 --> 01:57.826
- We found Dennis' tape.

02:02.247 --> 02:03.749
It's really water-damaged.

02:09.003 --> 02:10.797
- I can fix this.
JOE: Great.

02:10.797 --> 02:11.924
We gotta get it your dad's shop.

02:12.549 --> 02:14.551
- Okay, I'll drive us.
FENTON: Oh, come on.

02:14.551 --> 02:16.220
You've got to be kidding me.

02:16.220 --> 02:17.763
Do you have any idea what time it is?

02:17.763 --> 02:19.723
Go to bed. Let's go.

02:19.723 --> 02:21.725
Bed, alright?
Callie, I'll take you home.

02:21.725 --> 02:24.686
How about we see if
the front door still works?

02:24.686 --> 02:26.188
- Yeah. Uh, good call.

02:29.149 --> 02:31.026
I, um, didn't realize you'd be home.

02:31.026 --> 02:32.444
[insects continue chirping]

02:32.444 --> 02:33.946
- Where else would I be?

02:33.946 --> 02:36.949
♪

02:43.288 --> 02:44.790
[knocking]

02:44.790 --> 02:46.792
- Um, yeah, come in.

02:46.792 --> 02:48.669
[drawer shuts]
[door opens]

02:51.547 --> 02:54.675
- So, you and your friends just happened
to find Dennis at the school,

02:54.675 --> 02:56.176
right place, right time?

02:57.594 --> 02:58.929
- Is he gonna be okay?

02:59.972 --> 03:01.014
- I don't know.

03:01.014 --> 03:03.475
They've got a big-city
psychiatrist taking over.

03:03.976 --> 03:07.563
Whatever's going on, it's scary.

03:07.563 --> 03:10.148
[sighs] It's late.
You should go to bed.

03:10.649 --> 03:11.650
[kiss]

03:12.985 --> 03:14.486
- Hey, Mom?

03:14.945 --> 03:16.280
What were you like at 17?

03:16.989 --> 03:18.907
- [scoffs] I was a lot less tired.

03:24.329 --> 03:25.831
I worried a lot.

03:25.831 --> 03:26.999
♪

03:26.999 --> 03:28.500
About being accepted.

03:29.626 --> 03:31.128
About where I fit.

03:31.587 --> 03:32.963
[sighs]

03:32.963 --> 03:35.924
It's funny how things change.
- What do you mean?

03:36.508 --> 03:38.510
- Now, I just worry about you.

03:40.888 --> 03:43.891
[door creaks shut]

03:45.809 --> 03:47.311
[door shuts]
[keys jingle]

03:48.645 --> 03:50.439
MAN:
I understand, but we need to be careful.

03:50.439 --> 03:51.815
It's not a good idea to call my house.

03:52.941 --> 03:54.985
Come by my office tomorrow at lunch.
We'll take a ride.

03:54.985 --> 03:56.028
[hangs up phone]

03:59.865 --> 04:01.366
Hey! I didn't hear you come in.

04:01.366 --> 04:03.243
- Uh, who was on the phone?

04:04.411 --> 04:05.662
- No one. Work stuff.

04:07.039 --> 04:09.374
I was just making myself a sandwich.
You want a PB&J?

04:10.167 --> 04:11.668
- No J.

04:13.670 --> 04:15.464
- How was your night?

04:15.464 --> 04:18.007
- It was fun. Hung out with Chet.

04:19.091 --> 04:20.010
- Erica called.

04:20.594 --> 04:22.095
Again.

04:22.930 --> 04:25.057
Might wanna think about calling her back.

04:27.309 --> 04:29.394
You know, Gresham's is not that far away.
If it's the distance--

04:29.394 --> 04:30.687
- Dad!

04:30.687 --> 04:33.106
I know she was your favorite,
but it's over.

04:33.106 --> 04:35.317
- Let's set something straight.
You're my favorite.

04:36.276 --> 04:37.319
I just...

04:38.403 --> 04:39.905
I know it's hard to always be on the move.

04:40.614 --> 04:41.615
- Yeah.

04:43.242 --> 04:44.910
- So, what do I need to know about Chet?

04:44.910 --> 04:46.954
- He has a yellow truck.

04:46.954 --> 04:48.455
- Sounds incredible.
Can't wait to meet him.

04:48.455 --> 04:49.957
- [laughs] God...

04:52.334 --> 04:53.877
- I'm glad you're settling in here.

04:53.877 --> 04:55.838
♪

04:55.838 --> 04:57.339
- Me, too.

04:59.466 --> 05:01.844
DJ [on radio]:
And tomorrow night is the night.

05:01.844 --> 05:05.138
[car rumbling]
Demon Day Massacre at the Drive-In.

05:05.138 --> 05:07.558
[turns down volume]:
Get your tickets. Sure to be a fun

05:07.558 --> 05:09.977
and terrifying evening.
[music playing]

05:09.977 --> 05:11.520
- You seemed upset at the prison.

05:12.688 --> 05:16.024
But to be fair, my mother-in-law
has that effect on people.

05:16.024 --> 05:17.693
Hm.

05:17.693 --> 05:18.819
So, what do I need to know?

05:18.819 --> 05:20.988
Gloria threaten you?

05:20.988 --> 05:23.615
- No. No, nothing like that.

05:24.116 --> 05:26.410
- Okay.
- I made a mistake going there,

05:26.410 --> 05:27.870
and I lied to Frank about it.

05:28.912 --> 05:30.497
- Well, I think you did the right thing.

05:31.748 --> 05:33.000
- Deceiving your son?

05:33.750 --> 05:35.252
- Frank's been through a lot lately.

05:36.378 --> 05:38.380
You clearing your conscience, it's...

05:39.423 --> 05:41.091
not worth breaking his heart.

05:42.426 --> 05:44.303
- And what if Gloria tells him?

05:44.303 --> 05:47.264
- If she does that, she's got
nothing to hold over you. Mm-mmm.

05:47.264 --> 05:50.267
♪ indistinct singing on radio ♪

05:50.893 --> 05:52.895
Listen, I'm not saying
you keep this secret forever.

05:52.895 --> 05:55.647
I'm just saying keep it for now.

05:56.690 --> 05:59.693
♪

06:00.986 --> 06:03.989
♪ theme song ♪

06:14.041 --> 06:17.044
[rumbling]

06:17.044 --> 06:18.629
[brakes creak]

06:20.172 --> 06:21.173
[engine stops]

06:21.882 --> 06:23.634
[Belinda's Dad sighs]
[locks door]

06:24.384 --> 06:26.345
- Hey, Friday night.
Wanna do something fun tonight?

06:26.345 --> 06:27.596
- My dad wants to meet you.

06:28.388 --> 06:30.724
- See, I was thinking more
like movie at the Drive-In theat--

06:30.724 --> 06:33.101
- This looks great, but I meant now.
My dad wants to meet you right now.

06:33.101 --> 06:34.311
CHET:
Right now.

06:35.103 --> 06:36.271
- You must be Chet.

06:36.271 --> 06:38.524
- Yeah, hi.
Nice to meet you, Mr. Conrad.

06:38.524 --> 06:40.275
- Brian's fine.

06:40.275 --> 06:41.944
Belinda said you had a yellow truck.

06:41.944 --> 06:43.529
She didn't say it was such a beauty.

06:44.321 --> 06:47.324
I'm a bit of a car guy myself.
- Oh yeah?

06:47.324 --> 06:50.869
- Yeah. She's not flashy,
but she's safe and reliable.

06:51.662 --> 06:53.163
Fully loaded on the inside.

06:54.164 --> 06:56.792
- I mean, it's what's on the inside
that counts, right?

06:57.793 --> 06:59.545
- That's right.

06:59.545 --> 07:01.046
That's where it counts.

07:02.130 --> 07:03.340
So, what you got in there, Chet?

07:04.591 --> 07:06.468
- I feel like we're not talking
about cars anymore.

07:06.468 --> 07:07.970
- We are not.

07:08.762 --> 07:10.764
- And we have school! We good here?

07:12.641 --> 07:14.226
- I think so.

07:14.226 --> 07:15.978
We good? Chet?

07:17.104 --> 07:18.647
- Yeah, we're good.

07:19.314 --> 07:20.524
[taps car door]

07:21.567 --> 07:23.527
- Hey, uh, you wanna grab
some lunch later today?

07:23.527 --> 07:24.736
- I can't today.

07:24.736 --> 07:27.197
I've got a conference call
with the West Coast office.

07:27.197 --> 07:28.198
Stuck at my desk.

07:29.616 --> 07:31.743
[shuts car door]
- Your dad's cool.

07:31.743 --> 07:33.036
[starts engine]

07:33.036 --> 07:35.497
- He's lying to me.

07:35.497 --> 07:38.458
♪

07:38.458 --> 07:39.668
[machines beeping]

07:39.668 --> 07:41.712
JOE:
We knew someone was coming after him.

07:41.712 --> 07:43.797
We should have done more.

07:43.797 --> 07:44.882
FRANK:
How?

07:44.882 --> 07:46.884
Joe, we couldn't predict this.

07:48.385 --> 07:49.636
Whatever this is.

07:50.888 --> 07:52.598
Look at this list of meds.

07:52.598 --> 07:55.601
Zolpidem, lorazepam, benzodiazepine?

07:55.601 --> 07:58.604
- Those are all mainstay
treatments for his condition.

07:58.979 --> 08:01.481
And that's not for visitors.

08:01.481 --> 08:03.483
Are you family?
- Friends.

08:04.109 --> 08:05.986
We, uh, we found him last night.

08:05.986 --> 08:09.031
- Well, I'd actually prefer to
limit the number of people in and out.

08:09.031 --> 08:10.782
- Are you Dennis' new psychologist?

08:10.782 --> 08:13.452
- Psychiatrist, but yes.

08:13.452 --> 08:15.078
Dr. Burelli.

08:15.078 --> 08:16.580
Now, if you'll excuse me.

08:16.580 --> 08:19.583
[beeping continues]
[hospital chatter]

08:20.250 --> 08:21.668
- Is he going to be okay?

08:24.505 --> 08:26.006
- It's hard to say at this point.

08:26.673 --> 08:28.842
I'll know more when I can
initiate some therapies.

08:28.842 --> 08:31.220
♪

08:31.220 --> 08:33.514
Look, I can see you're worried
about your friend.

08:35.057 --> 08:36.308
So am I.

08:36.308 --> 08:39.561
He seems to be struggling
to process a critical event,

08:39.561 --> 08:42.397
a trauma he experienced or witnessed.

08:42.397 --> 08:44.983
- How can you go brain-dead
from something you see?

08:45.526 --> 08:47.277
- Well, he's not brain dead.

08:47.277 --> 08:48.487
Quite the opposite.

08:48.487 --> 08:50.906
His mind is in a state
of hyper-engagement.

08:51.990 --> 08:54.159
Dennis seems to be protecting himself

08:54.159 --> 08:55.327
- From what?

08:55.869 --> 08:58.330
- Whatever his mind perceives as a threat.

09:00.791 --> 09:02.292
Bye now.

09:05.671 --> 09:08.674
[indistinct PA announcement]

09:09.633 --> 09:11.134
[car rumbling]

09:11.134 --> 09:12.219
[engine stops]

09:12.970 --> 09:14.221
[street chatter]

09:14.221 --> 09:16.557
- What if you're protecting yourself, too?
Your visions?

09:16.557 --> 09:19.726
I mean, Dr. Burelli said Dennis' brain
is resisting a threat, right?

09:19.726 --> 09:20.853
So, what if yours is, too?

09:20.853 --> 09:22.187
- I'm not resisting anything.

09:22.187 --> 09:23.939
- Well yeah, not intentionally.

09:23.939 --> 09:25.649
But, there's a foreign entity
in your body.

09:25.649 --> 09:28.652
What if you're constantly fighting
the power of The Eye? And then the visions

09:28.652 --> 09:31.196
only happen when your defenses get
overwhelmed and something slips through?

09:31.989 --> 09:34.032
- It's not the craziest theory.

09:34.575 --> 09:36.493
- Maybe the key to controlling
the power is to let it in.

09:37.369 --> 09:38.453
[groans]
[ears ringing]

09:38.453 --> 09:40.664
[echo]: We need to let it.
[bang, thud, whirring]

09:40.664 --> 09:42.916
You'd be lost without me.
[ears ringing louder]

09:42.916 --> 09:44.418
[gasping]

09:45.419 --> 09:47.421
- We need to go
to Grandma's house at lunch.

09:47.421 --> 09:50.424
♪

09:52.092 --> 09:53.802
[opens door, bell rings]

09:53.802 --> 09:56.805
- Is it fixed yet?
- Morning to you, too.

09:56.805 --> 09:58.473
- Ignore him. He can't help himself.

09:58.473 --> 10:01.143
How's it going?
- I pulled the reel from the casing,

10:01.143 --> 10:02.644
spliced out what couldn't be salvaged,

10:02.644 --> 10:04.646
and soaked the rest
in a distilled water solution.

10:05.606 --> 10:07.774
- So yes.
- Well, no guarantee,

10:07.774 --> 10:09.234
but we'll know more when it dries.

10:09.234 --> 10:10.319
- How long does that take?

10:10.319 --> 10:12.321
- It's hard to say.
The books I read said anywhere

10:12.321 --> 10:14.865
between 14 and 18.
JOE: Oh, great.

10:14.865 --> 10:17.201
We can be a few minutes late for school.
- Hours, Joe.

10:17.201 --> 10:18.660
- What?!
- It's our best chance.

10:18.660 --> 10:21.163
We need dry, cool air
and constant ventilation.

10:21.163 --> 10:24.082
- You're drip drying it?
Just blast it with a hair dryer!

10:24.082 --> 10:26.293
- Do you wanna melt the tape?
- Can you set it on low?

10:27.294 --> 10:29.796
- Joe, we get one shot at this.
We can't afford to screw it up.

10:31.298 --> 10:33.759
- Alright, can we agree
on 14 hours at least then?

10:33.759 --> 10:36.220
I'll set my watch,
we'll meet here and take a look tonight.

10:36.220 --> 10:37.471
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

10:37.471 --> 10:38.972
[Joe sighs]

10:40.724 --> 10:42.100
What did you want to tell me last night?

10:42.100 --> 10:43.977
- Oh, um, it's nothing.

10:43.977 --> 10:45.771
I figured it out--
JOE: Hey, guys, let's go.

10:48.732 --> 10:49.566
[click]

10:49.566 --> 10:52.569
♪

11:02.162 --> 11:02.996
[click]

11:02.996 --> 11:03.956
♪ dramatic sting ♪

11:03.956 --> 11:05.666
[grunting, struggling]

11:06.083 --> 11:07.584
[panting]

11:08.252 --> 11:10.754
- You said you were good
at what you do, JB.

11:11.672 --> 11:14.967
This motel does not project
an image of success.

11:14.967 --> 11:17.427
- Yeah, well, they accept cash,

11:17.427 --> 11:19.429
and they don't ask any questions.

11:19.429 --> 11:21.723
But until you two snuck in,
I thought that was a good thing.

11:22.266 --> 11:23.684
- We had a deal.

11:23.684 --> 11:25.352
You find The Eye,

11:25.352 --> 11:26.979
you get to keep both of yours.
JB: Yeah.

11:27.479 --> 11:29.815
Have you ever heard the phrase
"patience is a virtue"?

11:30.482 --> 11:32.276
- Do it.
- No, no, no, no, no, no, no, no.

11:32.276 --> 11:35.654
Stop telling him to do things to me,
okay? Please. Just...

11:36.613 --> 11:39.616
The bug that I planted, it paid off.

11:39.616 --> 11:42.286
I've been listening in
for the last couple of days, and...

11:42.286 --> 11:44.121
honestly, the amount
of teen angst I've had to endure--

11:44.121 --> 11:45.122
- Skip to the end.

11:46.832 --> 11:49.042
- The Hardy Boys have The Eye.

11:50.502 --> 11:52.129
- Go get it.
JB: No, no--

11:52.129 --> 11:53.505
I didn't say they had it on them.

11:54.298 --> 11:55.591
It's somewhere. They've stashed it.

11:55.591 --> 11:57.217
I don't know exactly where--
[slice]

11:57.217 --> 11:58.177
- What good are you?

11:58.177 --> 11:59.678
[heavy breathing]

12:00.846 --> 12:03.098
- I have a plan. Okay?

12:05.475 --> 12:07.019
They trust me.

12:07.686 --> 12:08.937
- You have 24 hours.

12:09.897 --> 12:12.900
Or I'm going to come back
and give you a real close shave.

12:12.900 --> 12:15.819
♪

12:17.863 --> 12:18.864
[birds chirping]

12:18.864 --> 12:21.533
♪

12:21.533 --> 12:23.577
- So, what does your dad do anyway?

12:23.577 --> 12:24.953
- He's a consultant.

12:24.953 --> 12:26.955
He's, like, a numbers guy for companies.

12:26.955 --> 12:28.332
- Oh yeah?

12:28.332 --> 12:30.292
Does he just stare at
the numbers till they cooperate?

12:30.292 --> 12:31.543
[laughs]

12:33.170 --> 12:35.047
Oh, there he is. Get ready to go.

12:35.047 --> 12:36.048
[shuts door]

12:36.048 --> 12:38.300
- What is he doing?
Who's that in the car?

12:38.300 --> 12:40.469
BELINDA:
I don't know. Looks like a woman?

12:40.469 --> 12:43.430
I can't see her face though--
Get ready, Chet!

12:43.430 --> 12:44.640
- I'm ready. They haven't moved.

12:44.640 --> 12:46.475
[keys jingling]
BELINDA: Oh,

12:46.475 --> 12:48.101
I think he saw us.

12:48.101 --> 12:50.145
CHET: Is he walking this way?
Yeah, he's walking this way.

12:50.145 --> 12:51.688
- He's coming. He's coming. Just--

12:56.276 --> 12:57.277
- Hey.

12:57.277 --> 12:58.904
What are you doing here?

12:58.904 --> 13:00.322
- Just hangin'.

13:01.657 --> 13:03.200
- How's your conference call?

13:04.826 --> 13:07.412
- Chet, Belinda will see you later.

13:07.412 --> 13:09.790
Looks like she and I are going
to lunch today after all.

13:12.209 --> 13:15.212
[cars honking, street noise]

13:17.714 --> 13:19.466
So, what's good here?

13:20.425 --> 13:23.011
- Oh, I don't know.
I'm a pretty big fan of the truth.

13:23.011 --> 13:24.513
Who was the woman in the car?

13:24.513 --> 13:25.889
[radio playing]

13:25.889 --> 13:27.182
- She's a real estate agent.

13:28.517 --> 13:31.061
- We're moving again?
- Oh, honey, no.

13:31.061 --> 13:32.813
That came out wrong. She's...

13:32.813 --> 13:35.983
a real estate agent who I'm... dating.

13:36.900 --> 13:38.777
- But we've only been here a week.

13:38.777 --> 13:41.154
- Well, I was back and forth
a few times with her

13:41.154 --> 13:42.739
when we were looking for a place to rent,

13:42.739 --> 13:45.576
and we got to talking about other things,

13:45.576 --> 13:47.619
and it just kind of happened.

13:47.619 --> 13:48.745
- Why didn't you just tell me?

13:48.745 --> 13:50.163
[sighs]

13:50.163 --> 13:52.040
- You had a lot of big adjustments lately.

13:52.040 --> 13:53.125
I didn't wanna give you more

13:53.125 --> 13:54.668
than you could handle.
- I can handle it.

13:55.836 --> 13:57.921
- That's fair. I'm sorry.

13:57.921 --> 14:00.007
- We can be honest with each other, Dad.

14:00.007 --> 14:01.800
I won't freak out, okay?

14:04.178 --> 14:06.180
- Well, in that case,

14:06.180 --> 14:07.890
we are seeing each other tonight.

14:09.975 --> 14:12.853
- Wow. Uh... Okay. [scoffs]

14:12.853 --> 14:15.522
- Wait, I'm gonna read all about this
in your zine, aren't I?

14:15.522 --> 14:17.649
- Oh yeah. You better believe it.

14:18.192 --> 14:19.443
- Great.

14:19.443 --> 14:20.819
[laughs]

14:21.236 --> 14:22.863
♪

14:22.863 --> 14:24.990
JOE:
What are we looking for anyway?

14:24.990 --> 14:26.909
- Something to help control my visions.

14:26.909 --> 14:29.119
- Great. Super specific.

14:29.119 --> 14:30.913
Is it this?

14:31.705 --> 14:33.290
No.
[puts down magnifying glass]

14:33.290 --> 14:34.875
Okay. Is it...

14:35.667 --> 14:36.793
this?
[thud]

14:38.128 --> 14:39.880
♪ eerie music ♪

14:39.880 --> 14:40.839
[clicking, whirring]

14:41.465 --> 14:44.134
- Think I've seen that book in my visions.

14:54.436 --> 14:55.562
"The Way of the Mind,

14:55.562 --> 14:57.898
"how to reach an elevated
plane of consciousness

14:57.898 --> 15:01.276
through hypnosis, meditation,
and guided imagery."

15:01.276 --> 15:02.861
- Didn't know Great-Grandpa
was such a hippie.

15:04.488 --> 15:05.697
- Maybe he thought it would help him

15:05.697 --> 15:08.116
unlock more of The Eye's power.

15:08.116 --> 15:09.993
This page is marked.

15:14.122 --> 15:16.375
♪

15:16.375 --> 15:17.376
[Joe sighs]

15:19.086 --> 15:20.879
- You gonna share with the class?

15:22.548 --> 15:24.716
- "Guided imagery is
a mind-body intervention

15:24.716 --> 15:26.802
used to voluntarily reveal
or invoke a series--"

15:26.802 --> 15:29.263
- Okay. Stop. That's so much worse.

15:29.263 --> 15:31.431
Just give me the gist.

15:31.431 --> 15:32.641
- I need to clear my mind.

15:32.641 --> 15:35.102
- Oh. That should be easy.

15:37.437 --> 15:39.940
[creaking, footsteps]

15:39.940 --> 15:41.692
- Did you close the bookcase?

15:41.692 --> 15:43.694
- I gotta do everything around here?

15:43.694 --> 15:45.195
- You go.

15:50.951 --> 15:52.953
[Joe struggling]
Joe?

15:53.871 --> 15:56.456
[grunting]
Joe?

15:56.456 --> 15:59.668
[Joe panting]

15:59.668 --> 16:01.837
[gasping]

16:01.837 --> 16:02.921
♪

16:02.921 --> 16:04.089
Hey, hey, hey, don't hurt him!

16:04.089 --> 16:06.216
- Frank, they don't want me!
They want you!

16:06.216 --> 16:07.676
Go lock the door!

16:08.552 --> 16:09.553
[slam]

16:09.970 --> 16:12.347
- Stop, stop, stop!
You're gonna trigger the kill switch!

16:12.347 --> 16:14.600
[creaking]
Please listen to me! The door is rigged--

16:15.642 --> 16:17.186
[gasping]

16:17.186 --> 16:18.854
- You gonna share with the class?

16:21.398 --> 16:22.983
[beeping]

16:23.567 --> 16:25.319
MACK:
Angela.

16:25.319 --> 16:28.238
- Tell me you got something.
- The new coding worked.

16:28.238 --> 16:30.741
We locked onto the signal.
- Where?

16:30.741 --> 16:33.327
[static, hissing, beeping]

16:33.327 --> 16:34.912
MACK:
It's the Estabrook estate.

16:34.912 --> 16:36.330
♪

16:36.330 --> 16:38.582
- And to Grandmother's house we go.

16:40.626 --> 16:42.669
[school chatter]

16:42.669 --> 16:45.672
[typing]
- What did I say, Mr. Cohen?

16:45.672 --> 16:47.174
- The camera costs more than my house.

16:47.174 --> 16:48.634
- What happens if you lose it?

16:48.634 --> 16:51.136
- [sighs] The school's gonna cut
the AV budget, and then I'm gonna have

16:51.136 --> 16:52.763
to join school sports. I know.

16:52.763 --> 16:54.598
- Sign it back in first thing
in the morning

16:54.598 --> 16:56.934
and get the mic and tapes from
the AV room after class.

16:58.060 --> 16:59.811
You're late, Mr. Hardy.

16:59.811 --> 17:02.272
- Sorry, sir. Won't happen again.

17:02.272 --> 17:03.774
- Permit me to doubt that.

17:03.774 --> 17:06.359
[room chatter]

17:08.654 --> 17:10.989
We've got a million hours till the tape
dries at Callie's dad's shop.

17:10.989 --> 17:13.325
We should meet at the attic after
school and kick around some theories.

17:13.325 --> 17:15.035
- Can't. I've got tutoring.

17:15.035 --> 17:16.994
- Me neither. I gotta finish Dennis' film.

17:16.994 --> 17:18.579
I figured that's the least I could do.

17:18.579 --> 17:20.707
- Yeah, it's definitely
the least you could do.

17:20.707 --> 17:21.834
Why are we stepping off the gas?

17:21.834 --> 17:23.627
- We're not. We're killing time.

17:24.336 --> 17:25.420
It's going to be fun.

17:25.420 --> 17:28.715
- Oh. Oh, great. More waiting around,
only now with mosquitoes.

17:28.715 --> 17:30.551
- I thought the plan
is to wait for the tape.

17:30.551 --> 17:33.178
- Frank's plan is to wait for the tape.
I'm going to keep digging.

17:33.178 --> 17:35.806
- The last time you went rogue,
we almost ended up dead in a cave.

17:35.806 --> 17:37.391
- Okay, keyword almost.

17:37.391 --> 17:39.226
What about those lightning bolts
Dennis was drawing?

17:39.226 --> 17:41.103
That's got to be something, right?

17:41.103 --> 17:42.104
We need his notebook.

17:42.604 --> 17:44.064
- Doesn't Lucy have his notebook?

17:44.064 --> 17:46.066
[inaudible chatter]

17:46.066 --> 17:47.276
- Yeah, so?

17:47.276 --> 17:49.111
- So, Lucy hates you.

17:49.111 --> 17:51.238
- Well, nothing a little
Hardy charm can't handle.

17:52.114 --> 17:55.117
♪

17:55.117 --> 17:58.120
[hallway chatter]

17:59.705 --> 18:01.123
Hey, Lucy.

18:02.124 --> 18:04.835
Heading to the, uh, the Drive-In,
too, huh? Yeah,

18:04.835 --> 18:06.795
and I heard they shot on location, and--

18:06.795 --> 18:07.546
- Just take it.

18:08.130 --> 18:09.965
That's what you're here for, right?

18:11.175 --> 18:13.594
- Well, I mean, yeah, but--
- Thought so.

18:13.594 --> 18:14.595
[slams locker]

18:21.476 --> 18:22.895
- So, what's the status on your birth mom?

18:22.895 --> 18:25.439
- What, I didn't tell you? We're having
high tea tomorrow at The Plaza.

18:27.316 --> 18:28.817
I have her name, not her number.

18:28.817 --> 18:30.444
- You know that's what
a phone book's for, right?

18:30.903 --> 18:32.613
- I checked. She's not listed.

18:33.030 --> 18:34.740
- Did you check different cities?

18:37.117 --> 18:38.702
What are you waiting for?

18:39.369 --> 18:41.747
- I mean, it's kind of a big deal, Phil.

18:41.747 --> 18:43.415
I only get one shot at a first impression,

18:43.415 --> 18:45.125
and I want to do it right.

18:45.125 --> 18:46.752
What if I'm... I'm not--
[puts down book]

18:47.503 --> 18:49.630
- Lucy hates me.
BIFF: Told you.

18:49.630 --> 18:50.839
At least you got the notebook.

18:50.839 --> 18:52.799
- Yeah, but she thinks I only care
about the notebook.

18:52.799 --> 18:55.802
♪

18:56.261 --> 18:57.971
I'm trying to help her boyfriend!

18:57.971 --> 19:00.474
And what's the thanks I get?
I get a locker slammed in my face.

19:00.474 --> 19:02.935
- Dennis is in the hospital.
I think it's okay that she's upset.

19:02.935 --> 19:04.186
- Yeah, but why is she upset with me?

19:04.186 --> 19:06.230
- Because you're hyper-focusing
on solving the case

19:06.230 --> 19:09.149
instead of the more human,
emotional component?

19:09.858 --> 19:11.068
- No, that can't be it.

19:11.068 --> 19:13.237
- Why do you care so much what she thinks?
- I don't!

19:14.905 --> 19:16.406
I gotta go sort this out.

19:21.537 --> 19:22.913
[hallway chatter]
- Hey.

19:22.913 --> 19:24.957
- Just gotta swap out my binders,
and then I'm good to go.

19:25.582 --> 19:26.750
- Take your time.

19:26.750 --> 19:28.752
I'm not really in a rush
to be tutored on a Friday.

19:28.752 --> 19:31.797
GIRL: Like last year, they brought in
a stylist from Dixon City to do my makeup.

19:31.797 --> 19:33.340
It was rad.
[sighs]

19:33.340 --> 19:35.300
- Demon Queen two years in a row.

19:35.300 --> 19:38.512
Your parents must be so proud.
- I know, right?

19:38.512 --> 19:40.180
But, like, honestly,
who was going to beat me?

19:40.180 --> 19:41.515
Anyway, she let me keep a ton of stuff.

19:41.515 --> 19:44.560
It's too bad the gown was so grody.
Like, honestly, gag me with a spoon.

19:45.143 --> 19:46.061
[laughs]

19:49.982 --> 19:51.859
My mom was Demon Queen, too.

19:51.859 --> 19:53.819
- Ooh. Congrats to you.

19:53.819 --> 19:55.821
See you after detention, ladies.
[locker shuts]

19:55.821 --> 19:58.824
♪

20:02.786 --> 20:04.621
- Don't sweat Vanessa.

20:04.621 --> 20:06.748
She's popular,
but she's kind of the worst.

20:12.713 --> 20:14.214
♪

20:24.141 --> 20:26.143
[phone ringing]

20:28.937 --> 20:30.189
- Hardy residence.

20:30.189 --> 20:31.815
SAM [on phone]:
Did you get my package?

20:31.815 --> 20:33.358
- Yeah. Yeah, I'm looking at it right now.

20:33.942 --> 20:37.362
- McFarlane named his boat "Ellie,"
as in L-E.

20:38.197 --> 20:41.200
As in...
- Laura Estabrook. I got it.

20:41.200 --> 20:44.036
- Some guys can't let go of the past.

20:44.036 --> 20:45.871
Don't be that guy, Fent.

20:45.871 --> 20:47.289
[door opens]

20:47.289 --> 20:49.583
- Okay, gotta go. Thanks, Sam.
[shuts door]

20:49.583 --> 20:50.584
[hangs up]

20:51.543 --> 20:52.544
Hey.

20:53.754 --> 20:55.130
- Going back to Dixon City?

20:55.130 --> 20:56.423
- Yeah, I'm staying over.

20:56.423 --> 20:58.717
There's money for dinner
on the kitchen table.

20:58.717 --> 21:00.385
Try not to do pizza again, okay?

21:00.385 --> 21:02.137
Oh, and go easy on your aunt.

21:02.137 --> 21:04.389
She's stressed about
that whole demon dress thing.

21:04.389 --> 21:05.641
- Okay.
[door opens]

21:05.641 --> 21:07.726
- What time is this stupid
movie anyways?

21:07.726 --> 21:09.978
- Ah, Demon Night Massacre
at the Drive-In,

21:09.978 --> 21:11.438
- huh?
- Yeah.

21:12.523 --> 21:14.733
- Oh, come on. It's bad,
but it's bad in a good way.

21:14.733 --> 21:16.860
- No, it's not that. It's just I'm...

21:16.860 --> 21:18.820
I don't know. I'm having a hard time
wrapping my head around

21:18.820 --> 21:20.822
doing something normal
with everything that's going on.

21:20.822 --> 21:23.033
- Oh, come on, Frank.

21:23.033 --> 21:24.243
You're only 16 once.

21:24.243 --> 21:26.995
Not everything has to be
life and death all the time.

21:26.995 --> 21:29.289
You're allowed to have a little fun.
- Yeah.

21:29.289 --> 21:31.542
- I'm putting my bike in the trunk
so I can leave if it sucks.

21:33.126 --> 21:34.628
- He gets it.
[door opens]

21:34.628 --> 21:36.630
CALLIE:
What did you get for 14?

21:36.630 --> 21:39.550
- I got 1,234.
CALLIE: Remainder zero?

21:39.550 --> 21:41.510
- Yeah.
CALLIE: Perfect. Does that make sense?

21:41.510 --> 21:42.636
- Sure.

21:42.636 --> 21:45.138
Are we done?
- Yeah, we're done.

21:46.139 --> 21:48.767
Um, how you getting to the movie?
You want to ride with us?

21:48.767 --> 21:50.394
- I don't want to hijack your date.

21:50.394 --> 21:52.855
- Oh, it's not a date-date.
I mean, we're all hanging out.

21:52.855 --> 21:54.314
I think Joe is going to be there.

21:54.982 --> 21:57.276
- Okay, I'll come with you guys.

21:57.276 --> 21:58.986
- Red or peach?

21:59.361 --> 22:02.155
- Oh, um, I don't really...

22:02.155 --> 22:03.991
Lipstick or makeup.

22:03.991 --> 22:05.117
- No, that's okay. I mean,

22:05.117 --> 22:07.119
sometimes it's just fun
to play around with.

22:10.122 --> 22:12.249
I didn't know Jesse was
Demon Queen back in the day.

22:13.083 --> 22:15.586
- She wasn't. My birth mom was.

22:16.712 --> 22:18.255
I found out about the Demon Queen thing

22:18.255 --> 22:20.465
and it doesn't really line up
with what I had in my head.

22:20.465 --> 22:22.092
♪

22:22.092 --> 22:23.468
- What'd you have in your head?

22:24.094 --> 22:27.306
- I don't know.
Someone more like me, I guess.

22:27.848 --> 22:30.058
- Well, we're not our parents, right?

22:32.311 --> 22:34.688
Are you thinking about meeting her?

22:35.981 --> 22:37.900
- Thinking about it.

22:37.900 --> 22:41.028
Yeah. I just... I don't want
any disappointment.

22:42.237 --> 22:43.530
- For you or for her?

22:48.327 --> 22:50.829
BRIAN: Belinda, you have a guest!
- Okay, coming!

22:58.879 --> 23:00.881
Erica.
- Hey.

23:02.257 --> 23:03.509
- Have fun on your date, Dad.

23:03.509 --> 23:04.968
- Yeah, you, too.

23:05.844 --> 23:08.972
Well, what I meant...
[stammering] You know what?

23:08.972 --> 23:11.600
I'm just gonna--
Yeah, I'm just gonna go.

23:12.434 --> 23:13.852
Yeah.

23:13.852 --> 23:15.270
- You look amazing.

23:16.772 --> 23:19.107
What are you doing here?
- I told you.

23:19.942 --> 23:22.277
I missed you, B.
- We talked about this, Erica.

23:22.277 --> 23:24.530
We said we don't wanna do distance.
- I know what we said.

23:25.155 --> 23:27.282
I'm starting to think
it was stupid not to try.

23:27.282 --> 23:28.825
- I can't be in two places.

23:29.952 --> 23:32.120
- You met someone else?
- No.

23:32.120 --> 23:34.039
There's just a lot going on.

23:34.665 --> 23:37.626
- Then, let's go do something fun. Okay?

23:38.544 --> 23:41.630
Make everything that's going on
go away for a little while.

23:41.630 --> 23:43.924
♪

23:43.924 --> 23:45.425
[cuts engine]

23:46.218 --> 23:47.219
[grunts]

23:47.219 --> 23:50.222
[birds chirping]

23:52.099 --> 23:54.268
- I have to go.
- You're leaving?

23:55.769 --> 23:57.145
Just like that?

23:57.145 --> 23:59.106
I drove all the way here.

24:00.983 --> 24:03.151
- You shouldn't have.

24:05.612 --> 24:06.989
[door opens]

24:09.616 --> 24:12.244
CHET: Hey, who's your friend?
BELINDA: That's my ex.

24:12.828 --> 24:15.539
- Do you need to stay?
- No, I need to go. Let's just go.

24:17.291 --> 24:18.792
[car door shuts]
[Belinda sighs]

24:26.758 --> 24:29.928
♪

24:29.928 --> 24:32.931
[indistinct chatter]

24:33.974 --> 24:36.226
[rumbling]

24:39.229 --> 24:41.607
CALLIE:
How's the seat now? Is that okay?

24:41.607 --> 24:44.610
BIFF: Now, my leg's caught.
Um, Frank, can you move yours, too?

24:46.445 --> 24:49.489
- [grunts] That's as far as I'm moving--
Can you get your knee out of my back?

24:49.489 --> 24:51.450
BIFF: Sorry.
- Now, it's in my back, Biff.

24:51.450 --> 24:54.369
- Okay, well, I'm not doing this
for two hours. Can you let me out?

25:00.542 --> 25:03.712
[radio static]

25:03.712 --> 25:05.255
♪ indistinct singing ♪

25:07.174 --> 25:09.426
♪ I am exploring your mind ♪

25:10.052 --> 25:13.222
- Alright! I got drinks,
candy, popcorn, hot dogs,

25:13.222 --> 25:15.849
and a couple of ice cream sandwiches,
and, ah,

25:15.849 --> 25:18.352
I just realized I probably
should've got you something, too.

25:18.352 --> 25:19.853
- I'll take one of your
ice cream sandwiches.

25:19.853 --> 25:21.688
- Okay. So,

25:21.688 --> 25:24.024
you've had quite the day.
Wanna talk about any of it?

25:24.024 --> 25:26.026
- No, no. I just wanna watch the movie.

25:26.026 --> 25:28.362
- Did you guys see Joe
when you were getting snacks?

25:28.362 --> 25:30.531
- No.
- Is there room for one more?

25:31.114 --> 25:32.616
- No?
BELINDA: Yes!

25:32.616 --> 25:34.201
Of course there is.
Come on, we got lots of room.

25:35.369 --> 25:36.870
CHET:
Lots of room. Great.

25:38.163 --> 25:39.665
♪ A twist ♪

25:41.625 --> 25:43.460
- Are you gonna eat those
chocolate-covered raisins?

25:43.460 --> 25:44.461
- Nope...

25:44.461 --> 25:46.588
♪ Ooh... ♪

25:49.842 --> 25:52.845
♪

25:54.179 --> 25:56.390
- Hey, Lucy. Got a second to talk?

25:56.390 --> 25:58.016
- You need a hobby, Joe.

25:59.935 --> 26:01.645
- Just trying to help your boyfriend.

26:01.645 --> 26:03.689
- Are you?

26:03.689 --> 26:06.400
'Cause it seems like you
only care about Dennis

26:06.400 --> 26:08.402
because something messed up
happened to him.

26:09.403 --> 26:11.613
Did you even know who he was before that?

26:11.613 --> 26:14.116
- So what? He needed my help.

26:14.783 --> 26:18.287
I mean, some people
send flowers or write cards.

26:18.871 --> 26:21.206
That doesn't find someone in the woods.

26:21.206 --> 26:24.126
I know what it's like to lose someone,

26:24.126 --> 26:26.962
so I don't want anybody to lose anyone.

26:26.962 --> 26:29.089
Not if I can help it.

26:29.089 --> 26:32.551
So, I-I press on every lead
and every suspect,

26:32.551 --> 26:34.136
and I don't want to be judged for it

26:34.136 --> 26:35.929
because I already have
enough people in my life

26:35.929 --> 26:38.390
telling me to slow down and act normal.

26:38.390 --> 26:40.475
And I know you don't like being a suspect,

26:40.475 --> 26:43.770
but if I don't look at everybody,
then things get missed,

26:43.770 --> 26:46.148
and that's when people get hurt. So,

26:46.148 --> 26:48.817
in a weird way,
I'm doing this for you, too.

26:48.817 --> 26:51.820
[chatter continues]

26:52.529 --> 26:54.531
- The movie is going to start soon.

26:55.282 --> 26:56.742
Are you going to sit?

26:57.910 --> 26:59.203
- I'll sit.

26:59.203 --> 27:00.704
♪

27:05.375 --> 27:06.418
- Blanket?

27:07.503 --> 27:09.004
- Uh, sure.

27:12.508 --> 27:14.510
♪ swelling ♪

27:14.510 --> 27:16.512
♪

27:26.563 --> 27:28.315
[inaudible]

27:30.984 --> 27:33.111
GIRL IN MOVIE: Jimmy?

27:33.111 --> 27:35.364
Jimmy, is that you?

27:35.364 --> 27:37.241
Jimmy, cut it out. You're scaring me.

27:37.241 --> 27:40.244
[wind blowing]
[animal growling]

27:40.244 --> 27:43.705
[girl screaming]
[snarling, eating]

27:43.705 --> 27:46.375
♪ cheesy music ♪

27:46.375 --> 27:47.876
[siren onscreen]

27:50.003 --> 27:52.589
[man panting onscreen]

27:52.589 --> 27:55.050
[man groaning onscreen]
[sirens get louder]

27:55.050 --> 27:56.635
MOVIE MAN:
Hey! Hey!

27:56.635 --> 27:59.221
- I'm going to go get a refill.
Be right back.

27:59.221 --> 28:00.722
MAN IN MOVIE:
L-look out!

28:01.473 --> 28:03.100
[gunshot]
Get down!

28:03.100 --> 28:04.601
Get outta here!

28:04.601 --> 28:07.604
♪

28:10.399 --> 28:11.733
[shuts door]

28:12.025 --> 28:13.026
[clang]

28:13.610 --> 28:15.654
[struggling with door]

28:16.321 --> 28:18.031
[grunting, groaning]

28:19.032 --> 28:21.743
[struggling, clattering]

28:22.786 --> 28:25.622
[grunts]

28:25.622 --> 28:27.624
- Nice hook, Frank. [gasps]

28:28.375 --> 28:30.377
- JB.
- Yeah. [panting]

28:30.377 --> 28:31.753
You owe me a new pair of shades.

28:31.753 --> 28:34.840
- What are you doing here?
Were you following me?

28:34.840 --> 28:37.342
[projector whirring]
- [panting] You and Joe...

28:37.342 --> 28:38.886
need to give me The Eye.

28:38.886 --> 28:40.470
Okay? And then you both
need to get out of town.

28:40.470 --> 28:43.473
- We don't have it, and we can't exactly
leave town. We kinda live here.

28:43.473 --> 28:46.768
- Well if you want to keep living,
then you will get gone

28:46.768 --> 28:48.020
while the getting gone is good.

28:48.020 --> 28:50.147
It's not safe here anymore.

28:50.147 --> 28:51.940
FRANK: If it's not safe here,
what are you still doin' here?

28:51.940 --> 28:53.984
- I don't have a choice.

28:53.984 --> 28:55.611
You do.

28:55.611 --> 28:57.154
Aren't you supposed to be the--

28:57.154 --> 29:00.115
the rational older brother,
makes the right decisions?

29:01.408 --> 29:04.161
Look, if you're so hellbent
on sticking around, fine.

29:04.161 --> 29:06.788
Be my guest, but be smart.

29:06.788 --> 29:09.750
Stop using The Eye!
- We don't have it!

29:09.750 --> 29:11.752
- Except I know you do.

29:12.252 --> 29:14.505
And the more you use it,
the more you're putting yourself

29:14.505 --> 29:16.298
and everybody you care about at risk.

29:16.298 --> 29:19.009
- What are you talking about?
- I'm talking about Stratemeyer.

29:19.009 --> 29:20.844
♪

29:20.844 --> 29:21.887
They can trace it.

29:23.597 --> 29:24.515
Yeah.

29:24.515 --> 29:26.892
Whatever energy
is coming off of that relic,

29:26.892 --> 29:28.268
they figured out a way to lock onto it,

29:28.268 --> 29:31.230
so the next time you use it, they'll know.

29:32.231 --> 29:33.732
Don't say I didn't warn you.

29:35.859 --> 29:38.862
♪

29:40.906 --> 29:42.991
[insects chirping]
[door opens]

29:43.909 --> 29:47.120
- Where's your drink? Are you okay?
- [sighs] Are we cursed?

29:47.871 --> 29:50.374
Anya Kowalski said the ground
that we walked on is cursed,

29:50.374 --> 29:51.625
that our lives would be cursed, too.

29:51.625 --> 29:53.877
- Anya Kowalski's a two-bit
fortune teller.

29:53.877 --> 29:55.921
Why are you thinking about Anya Kowalski?

29:55.921 --> 29:57.172
- I don't want to be a danger to you.

29:58.632 --> 29:59.675
- You're not.

29:59.675 --> 30:01.468
- You were kidnapped.

30:01.468 --> 30:02.845
We were almost murdered.

30:02.845 --> 30:07.224
Everything in my life is secrets
and lies and murder and mayhem,

30:07.224 --> 30:09.059
and I keep waiting
for things to be normal,

30:09.059 --> 30:10.394
but I don't think they ever will be.

30:12.145 --> 30:14.314
And I think if you would have known that--
- Frank.

30:14.314 --> 30:16.400
the first time we hung out alone,

30:16.400 --> 30:18.610
your grandma trapped us
in a room full of puzzles

30:18.610 --> 30:20.779
as an initiation into a secret society

30:20.779 --> 30:24.157
that kills people to protect
an ancient, magical artifact.

30:25.993 --> 30:28.203
Trust me, I knew.

30:28.871 --> 30:31.790
I hate to break it to you,
but normal isn't normal for us.

30:34.168 --> 30:36.003
And I like us.

30:36.712 --> 30:38.505
- I like us, too.

30:41.925 --> 30:42.926
[kiss]

30:42.926 --> 30:45.929
[movie chatter continues]

30:48.473 --> 30:51.476
♪ cheesy scary movie music ♪

30:51.476 --> 30:52.978
[monster panting]

30:52.978 --> 30:54.104
MAN IN MOVIE:
Look out!

30:54.104 --> 30:57.107
[woman screaming]

30:58.734 --> 31:00.986
They're neither living nor dead.

31:02.196 --> 31:05.073
They have no feelings. No empathy.

31:06.783 --> 31:08.619
They're worse than animals.

31:10.162 --> 31:11.872
They are the undead.

31:11.872 --> 31:13.540
[growling]

31:13.540 --> 31:17.169
They're driven by an insatiable,
evil hunger. They are everywhere.

31:17.169 --> 31:19.379
[growling]

31:20.047 --> 31:21.757
LUCY:
Maybe we should talk about something.

31:21.757 --> 31:23.425
[turns off movie audio]
JOE: Oh, yeah, sure, okay.

31:24.843 --> 31:26.678
- Do you still think I'm a suspect, Joe?

31:28.305 --> 31:30.516
- Don't know what to think about you.

31:30.516 --> 31:33.519
[movie chatter continues]

31:34.144 --> 31:36.146
- I went into the woods
with Dennis that night.

31:37.022 --> 31:38.315
We had a fight.

31:39.191 --> 31:41.360
I broke up with him...
[screaming in movie]

31:41.360 --> 31:42.736
and I left.

31:44.196 --> 31:45.822
- And he didn't remember anything.

31:48.200 --> 31:50.327
- He didn't even remember
that I was there.

31:50.953 --> 31:53.372
I left him in the woods alone.

31:53.372 --> 31:55.916
- It's not your fault.
- It is.

31:55.916 --> 31:59.419
When he didn't come home,
I thought he was just being dramatic.

31:59.419 --> 32:02.798
So, I didn't tell you where he was filming
or that I was with him.

32:04.216 --> 32:06.218
But when you found him in the West Woods

32:07.219 --> 32:09.221
and his pin was in that shack,

32:10.681 --> 32:12.683
I knew something was really wrong.

32:14.893 --> 32:16.895
I wanted you to get
to the truth. I just...

32:19.356 --> 32:21.358
I didn't want him to remember everything.

32:22.276 --> 32:24.736
- You didn't want to hurt him again.

32:25.362 --> 32:28.365
[movie screaming]

32:28.365 --> 32:30.242
- Everything's so messed up, Joe.

32:30.826 --> 32:32.244
- It's going to be okay.

32:33.287 --> 32:34.329
- How?

32:34.746 --> 32:37.624
[watch beeping]

32:37.624 --> 32:39.334
[beeping stops]
JOE: Um...

32:39.334 --> 32:40.919
I-I-I'm so sorry.

32:40.919 --> 32:43.922
I-I-I have to go,
but we can-- we can talk later?

32:44.631 --> 32:46.550
- What? The movie's not even over yet.

32:46.550 --> 32:49.219
- I know, I just-- I gotta figure out
who did this, okay?

32:49.636 --> 32:51.138
I know it wasn't you.

32:51.138 --> 32:54.141
♪

32:55.350 --> 32:58.353
[inaudible]

32:59.479 --> 33:01.899
FRANK: Do you ever miss
what life was like before?

33:02.441 --> 33:04.443
You know, before we uncovered the truth.

33:04.443 --> 33:07.154
[movie chatter]

33:07.154 --> 33:08.780
- No, it's...

33:08.780 --> 33:10.782
It's always better
to know the truth, right?

33:12.326 --> 33:14.828
- I never would have made it
through the last year without you.

33:14.828 --> 33:16.246
♪

33:16.246 --> 33:18.749
- You're giving me too much credit.
- No.

33:20.042 --> 33:21.460
No, Callie.

33:22.669 --> 33:24.671
You're brave,

33:24.671 --> 33:26.465
you're smart,

33:26.465 --> 33:28.008
and you're relentless.

33:28.008 --> 33:29.009
[quiet laugh]

33:29.718 --> 33:31.720
I don't know what I would do without you.

33:35.891 --> 33:37.518
- I went to go see Gloria.

33:38.936 --> 33:41.146
[running footsteps]

33:41.146 --> 33:43.065
- Tape's ready, let's go!

33:43.065 --> 33:45.692
What are you waiting for?
Open the trunk, I got to put my bike in.

33:47.277 --> 33:48.654
[door opens]

33:49.071 --> 33:52.991
PHIL: You will find what will dread
the most dead of the dead.

33:52.991 --> 33:54.993
[tape hissing]
Beware...

33:54.993 --> 33:57.037
the Bridgeport Demon.

33:57.621 --> 34:00.457
And cut. Nice.
[clicking, tape stops]

34:02.709 --> 34:03.710
[sighs] Okay.

34:03.710 --> 34:06.505
[flipping pages]

34:08.422 --> 34:10.425
[wind blowing outside]

34:11.760 --> 34:13.262
[knocking]
Uh, come in.

34:15.054 --> 34:17.766
- Dad wanted me to bring you this
since you're missing out on the Drive-In.

34:17.766 --> 34:19.560
- Thanks.
[puts down bowl]

34:19.560 --> 34:20.893
TIFFANY:
What you working on anyway?

34:20.893 --> 34:23.063
- Oh, I'm just finishing Dennis' movie.

34:23.063 --> 34:24.313
TIFFANY:
Really? Why?

34:25.065 --> 34:27.317
Didn't he, like,
un-invite you to his birthday?

34:27.317 --> 34:28.485
- Yes.

34:29.444 --> 34:30.696
- So, why are you helping him?

34:30.696 --> 34:32.947
- It's called being a nice person.
Maybe you should try it sometime.

34:32.947 --> 34:34.783
- Oh. [scoffs] Whatever.

34:35.701 --> 34:38.203
- Stop, you're gonna ruin it!
- Your face ruins it.

34:38.661 --> 34:40.831
Good night, Philly.
[shuts door]

34:40.831 --> 34:43.833
♪

34:43.833 --> 34:45.835
[car driving by outside]

34:50.132 --> 34:51.717
[continues scraping]

34:51.717 --> 34:54.719
[stops scraping]
[car drives by]

34:58.473 --> 35:00.392
- Joe, me and Callie
need a minute to talk.

35:00.392 --> 35:02.186
JOE:
About what? We got to get the tape.

35:02.186 --> 35:03.604
- Joe, just give us a minute, please.

35:04.188 --> 35:07.065
- Great, it's a whole thing. Sure.
Why not? It's only been 700 minutes.

35:07.065 --> 35:08.859
- We'll catch you in there.

35:08.859 --> 35:11.862
[street chatter]

35:12.696 --> 35:14.698
[unlocks door, bell rings]

35:17.242 --> 35:18.994
[person rummaging]

35:18.994 --> 35:20.495
[door shuts]

35:25.501 --> 35:28.295
[rummaging]
- [quietly]: Mr. Shaw?

35:29.087 --> 35:32.090
♪

35:32.674 --> 35:34.218
[smashing]

35:35.052 --> 35:38.347
[slamming, banging]

35:40.140 --> 35:41.433
[wood breaking]

35:44.770 --> 35:46.104
[gasping]

35:48.357 --> 35:49.900
[crash]

35:55.572 --> 35:58.742
- We both decided that we would
cut Gloria out of our lives.

35:58.742 --> 36:00.035
- No, you decided.

36:00.744 --> 36:03.580
I've been close with Gloria for years.
I needed to get closure.

36:03.580 --> 36:06.124
- You didn't go for closure.
You went to get into prep school.

36:06.834 --> 36:08.919
Why do you want it so bad?
- It means a better life.

36:08.919 --> 36:10.879
- Yeah, but it also means that
you're gonna be away from me.

36:10.879 --> 36:13.590
Why are you fighting for that?
- It's not about you.

36:13.590 --> 36:16.760
[running]
JOE: I saw him! The guy that hurt Dennis!

36:16.760 --> 36:19.012
He was at your shop. He attacked me.
- What?

36:19.012 --> 36:20.639
- How did he know where it was?

36:20.639 --> 36:23.058
- That's your first question?
I barely got away with my life!

36:23.058 --> 36:24.810
FRANK: Are you okay?
JOE: Yeah, no. I-I couldn't get

36:24.810 --> 36:27.271
all the tape. He was desperate.
There must be something on here.

36:27.271 --> 36:29.231
We gotta get home and watch this.

36:29.231 --> 36:33.068
[doors shut]
[starts car, revs engine]

36:33.068 --> 36:36.071
♪

36:36.071 --> 36:39.074
[dog barking outside]

36:44.162 --> 36:46.874
JESSE:
Biff? Phil's here for some reason!

36:46.874 --> 36:49.710
Even though it's very late...
- Okay!

36:49.710 --> 36:52.713
JESSE: He's coming up!
[footsteps]

36:55.048 --> 36:56.967
- I found something.

36:56.967 --> 36:59.052
Is that lipstick?
- What do you want, Phil?

36:59.052 --> 37:00.596
- There's a page ripped
outta Dennis' notebook.

37:00.596 --> 37:02.472
He drew a circle and a lightning bolt.

37:02.472 --> 37:04.391
I think Dennis remembered
something from the other night,

37:04.391 --> 37:06.059
something someone
didn't want him to remember.

37:06.059 --> 37:07.394
♪

37:07.394 --> 37:09.646
So, they silenced him.

37:11.773 --> 37:14.151
[door shuts]
- [sighs] Thank you for the ride home.

37:14.985 --> 37:17.529
And the movie. It was nice to just...

37:17.529 --> 37:19.531
turn my brain off for a bit.

37:20.532 --> 37:23.035
- Listen, I don't want to make
any assumptions or anything,

37:23.035 --> 37:25.037
but I'm starting to think
that your ex-girlfriend

37:25.037 --> 37:27.331
didn't fall to her death after all.
[Belinda laughs]

37:28.290 --> 37:30.250
- What was your first clue?

37:30.250 --> 37:32.920
- I mean, the way she kind of
showed up out of nowhere

37:32.920 --> 37:35.797
was kind of a pretty big giveaway.
- Yeah...

37:37.049 --> 37:39.801
- Listen, if you're still into her--
- I'm not!

37:39.801 --> 37:40.802
- Okay.

37:40.802 --> 37:42.930
I'm just saying, I get it.

37:43.972 --> 37:47.059
Just because something is over
doesn't mean it all goes away.

37:47.726 --> 37:49.853
Some things just kinda...

37:49.853 --> 37:51.855
stick with you, you know?

37:53.815 --> 37:55.317
- Yeah. [inhales]

37:56.401 --> 37:58.612
I just never know where I'm gonna be,

37:58.612 --> 37:59.988
or for how long,

37:59.988 --> 38:03.158
so I just need to be where I am.

38:03.158 --> 38:05.285
With the people I'm with.

38:05.285 --> 38:07.913
And I like being here. [laughs]

38:11.333 --> 38:13.001
- Me, too.

38:14.962 --> 38:17.256
[footsteps]
[gasps, clears throat]

38:17.256 --> 38:19.675
- [sighs] Hey. How was the movie?

38:19.675 --> 38:22.261
- Really bad and really good.

38:22.261 --> 38:23.679
- Just how I like 'em.

38:23.679 --> 38:25.889
- Uh, I thought you had a date.
BRIAN: Yeah, I'm on it.

38:25.889 --> 38:28.100
We came back here for coffee.

38:28.100 --> 38:30.769
And as long as we're all here...

38:30.769 --> 38:34.648
Belinda, this is my friend Angela. Ange,

38:34.648 --> 38:37.693
this is my daughter, Belinda.
ANGELA: It's nice to finally meet.

38:37.693 --> 38:41.363
I've heard so much about you, Belinda.
- And that's her friend, Chet.

38:41.363 --> 38:44.366
♪

38:45.576 --> 38:48.245
[insects chirping]

38:48.620 --> 38:51.582
CALLIE: Okay. Here goes.
[clicking]

38:52.040 --> 38:53.041
[presses play]

38:53.584 --> 38:55.294
[sighs]
[tape starts]

38:55.294 --> 38:57.087
DENNIS [on tape]:
The sun sets over the West Woods.

38:57.629 --> 39:01.258
A majestic contrast to the evil
the demon's about to unleash.

39:01.258 --> 39:02.050
[hiss]

39:02.050 --> 39:04.052
- What happened?
- It's where I spliced the tape.

39:05.345 --> 39:07.055
FRANK:
That's Tom Elroy's shack.

39:08.807 --> 39:11.768
What is all that?
JOE: Can't tell. It's too scrambled.

39:11.768 --> 39:13.020
- That's the water damage.

39:13.020 --> 39:15.272
- Why's it damaged at
the worst possible time?

39:15.939 --> 39:18.942
FRANK: Wait, look.
That's the flour that we found.

39:18.942 --> 39:21.403
- Whoa, whoa, whoa! Go back. Go back.
Someone's there.

39:21.403 --> 39:23.280
[rewinding, playing]

39:23.280 --> 39:24.865
FRANK:
Can you guys tell who that is?

39:24.865 --> 39:26.825
JOE:
No. Dennis ducks down too fast.

39:26.825 --> 39:28.744
- Hold on. He's coming back up.

39:28.744 --> 39:30.245
Look.

39:30.245 --> 39:32.706
The person's over there by a... a map.

39:32.706 --> 39:35.167
♪

39:35.167 --> 39:37.127
They're gonna draw something...

39:37.836 --> 39:39.713
[hissing]
- Oh, come on!

39:40.589 --> 39:41.924
CALLIE:
He's being chased!

39:41.924 --> 39:43.717
He must have been spotted at the window.

39:43.717 --> 39:45.802
- Dennis definitely saw something
he wasn't supposed to.

39:45.802 --> 39:49.056
[panting, grunting, heavy breathing]

39:50.599 --> 39:51.600
♪

39:52.726 --> 39:53.727
[VCR squeaking]

39:53.727 --> 39:55.646
- What just happened? Is that it?!
[clicking]

39:55.646 --> 39:58.524
- That's the end of the roll. Rewind it.
[click]

39:58.524 --> 40:01.026
[rewinding]

40:01.026 --> 40:03.070
FRANK:
Here. That's a map of our town, right?

40:03.070 --> 40:04.363
You can tell by the waterfront.

40:04.363 --> 40:05.113
[click]

40:05.113 --> 40:07.032
[VCR whirring]

40:07.574 --> 40:08.909
JOE:
What are those tubes?

40:09.326 --> 40:10.661
Pipes?

40:10.661 --> 40:11.912
Oh, those are fireworks.

40:11.912 --> 40:13.121
What's that white thing beside it?

40:13.121 --> 40:15.624
CALLIE: That's a water jug.
See, it says "H2O."

40:15.624 --> 40:16.667
No, wait.

40:17.167 --> 40:19.127
That says "H2O2."

40:21.213 --> 40:22.673
That's hydrogen peroxide.

40:24.007 --> 40:26.176
- Dennis saw someone making a bomb.

40:26.176 --> 40:29.137
There's gonna be an attack on Bridgeport.

40:29.137 --> 40:31.890
♪ tense music ♪

40:32.891 --> 40:35.894
♪
